    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nNo\n\n### Feature description\n\nHi, my request is regarding LSP support in neovim but it's not specific to any of the LSP servers.\r\nWhen qflist is populated with diagnostics, the order of entries is determined by buffer number and line number.\r\nHere's the sorting function: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua#L1606\r\nSome(if not all) LSP servers send diagnostics in a particular order and I don't get why neovim would try to reorder them.\r\nI'd suggest adding an option to provide your own sorting function(or simply allow to not sort the entries).",
